Enum RegistryExporter.Format

  • java.lang.Object

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    public static enum RegistryExporter.Format
extends Enum<RegistryExporter.Format>

    Specifies the type of format to use when saving registry information.

    Since:
    1.2
    Version:
    1.8
    Author:
    Yinon Michaeli

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      REGEDIT4
      The old format that is used on Windows 9x/NT.
      REGEDIT5
      The new format that is used on Windows 2000/XP/Vista/7.
      TEXT
      A text format which is used to give some information about the keys that were saved such the last time the key was written to and also its class name if one was set.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • REGEDIT5

        public static final RegistryExporter.Format REGEDIT5
        The new format that is used on Windows 2000/XP/Vista/7. This format is not compatible with Windows 9x/NT.
        See Also:
        REGEDIT4

      • REGEDIT4

        public static final RegistryExporter.Format REGEDIT4
        The old format that is used on Windows 9x/NT. It is provided for use on Windows 2000/XP/Vista/7 because of backwards compatibility.
        See Also:
        REGEDIT5

      • TEXT

        public static final RegistryExporter.Format TEXT
        A text format which is used to give some information about the keys that were saved such the last time the key was written to and also its class name if one was set.

        Note that this format cannot be imported into the Windows Registry.
